Thus the whole line should be, “ and rises to a greater name for nobleness in the case of those who act worthily of their birth.'' That is, “ He is noble who is nobly born ς but the nobleman who acts nobly is the noblest of all.” So Shakspeare (All’s Well that Ends well, ii. 3) says, conversely,
